Special Adviser on Media and Public Affairs to Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal of Sokoto State, Imam Imam is dead. He died after a brief illness. Imam, who died on Friday, 27th April was the first appointee of Governor Tambuwal few hours after he was sworn in as governor in 2015. He had served in the same capacity when Tambuwal was the Speaker of the House of Representatives from 2011. Imam, a former Group Politics Editor at THISDAY Newspapers, was born on July 16, 1977 in Gboko, Benue State but hails from Taraba State. He will be buried later today in accordance with the Islamic faith. 1 comments